---
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Lund Covenant — Greg Maxfield" description="A novel of the American West. When Gill Lund returns to Castle Dale, Utah after his father's death, he intends to stay three days." image="/images/og-image.png">

<!-- BOOK HERO -->
<section class="book-page-hero">
  <img
    src="/images/tlc-cover-front.jpg"
    alt="The Lund Covenant by Greg Maxfield"
    width="320"
    height="480"
    transition:name="tlc-cover"
    transition:animate="initial"
  />
  <h1>The Lund Covenant</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A Novel</p>
  <p class="byline">by Greg Maxfield</p>
  <div class="buy-buttons">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Pre-Order on Amazon</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">Order from Bookshop.org</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FULL BLURB -->
<section class="book-page-blurb reveal">
  <p>
    When Gill Lund returns to Castle Dale, Utah after his father's death, he intends to stay three days.
    Long enough to bury the man, settle the estate, and go back to the life he built on the other side
    of twelve years and a lot of open country.
  </p>
  <p>The town has other plans.</p>
  <p>
    His father — quiet, stubborn, not a man who explained himself — had been driving into the desert
    at odd hours, tending water caches hidden in the San Rafael Swell. Desert travelers in desperate need.
    Small mercies, unmarked and unannounced. Until someone found them and destroyed them, methodically,
    with bleach and a serrated blade.
  </p>
  <p>
    The evidence leads somewhere no one in Castle Dale wants to look. And the more Gill asks, the more
    he understands that his father's silence wasn't indifference — it was the posture of a man who had
    already paid the cost of speaking plainly in a small town, and who kept doing the work anyway.
  </p>
  <p>
    Gill is a photojournalist. He knows how to document things. What he doesn't know yet is whether
    he's willing to be part of the story.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- ABOUT THE BOOK -->
<section class="book-page-about">
  <div class="inner reveal">
    <h2>About the Book</h2>
    <p>
      <em>The Lund Covenant</em> is a novel about moral inheritance — the obligations that place imposes,
      the cost of bearing witness, and what changes when a man decides to stay. Set in the high desert of
      Emery County, Utah, it follows a photojournalist's reckoning with a small Mormon community fracturing
      under the weight of a secret that was never meant to surface.
    </p>
    <p>
      Literary fiction with a suspense spine, <em>The Lund Covenant</em> belongs on the shelf next to
      Kent Haruf's <em>Plainsong</em>, Ron Rash's <em>Serena</em>, Marilynne Robinson's <em>Gilead</em>,
      and Paulette Jiles's <em>News of the World</em>.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--color-text-light); font-size:0.95rem; margin-top:1.5rem;">
      ~82,000 words &middot; Paperback &amp; Ebook &middot; July 2026
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ENDORSEMENTS (placeholder) -->
<section class="endorsements reveal">
  <h2>Praise</h2>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
  <div class="endorsement-slot">
    <p>"Endorsement quote placeholder — to be populated from ARC reviews."</p>
    <p><strong>— Reviewer Name, Source</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- REPEATED BUY LINKS -->
<section style="text-align:center; padding:2rem 1.5rem 1rem;">
  <div class="buy-buttons">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Pre-Order on Amazon</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-secondary">Order from Bookshop.org</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-ghost">Add on Goodreads</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- NEWSLETTER CTA (matches homepage #subscribe) -->
<section class="subscribe-section">
  <div class="container content-narrow reveal" style="text-align:center;">
    <h2>Get the First Three Chapters Free</h2>
    <p>Sign up for launch updates and receive the opening chapters of <em>The Lund Covenant</em> — delivered to your inbox.</p>
    <div class="email-embed-placeholder" style="padding:2rem; border:2px dashed rgba(250,248,245,0.3); border-radius:8px; margin-top:1.5rem;">
      <p style="color:rgba(250,248,245,0.6); font-style:italic; margin:0;">ConvertKit signup form — coming soon</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  // U5: Scroll-reveal for book page
  const reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const revealObserver = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        revealObserver.unobserve(entry.target);
      }
    });
  }, { rootMargin: '0px 0px -80px 0px' });
  reveals.forEach(el => revealObserver.observe(el));
</script>

</Layout>
